-xl"><div aria-label="View A clean, minimal strategy-clicker game interface showing a flat 2D map of Europe divided into multiple colored sub‑regions (small provinces). Each major country has several provinces in different shades of one color. Northern Africa is visible at the bottom with its own colored provinces. At the top of the screen, a very small minimalist resource bar appears: tiny icons for gold, wood, stone, food, population, and soldiers, each with a small number next to it. The map fills almost the entire screen. Provinces have clear borders and soft color tones. The style is simple, modern, and game‑ready, with no UI clutter and no text panels or metadata on the sides. in full screen" class="group relative overflow-hidden rounded-[14px] cursor-pointer w-full" data-image-card="0" style="width: 100%; max-width: 100%; max-height: 600px; aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;"><img alt="A clean, minimal strategy-clicker game interface showing a flat 2D map of Europe divided into multiple colored sub‑regions (small provinces). Each major country has several provinces in different shades of one color. Northern Africa is visible at the bottom with its own colored provinces. At the top of the screen, a very small minimalist resource bar appears: tiny icons for gold, wood, stone, food, population, and soldiers, each with a small number next to it. The map fills almost the entire screen. Provinces have clear borders and soft color tones. The style is simple, modern, and game‑ready, with no UI clutter and no text panels or metadata on the sides." class="size-full scale-[1.15] rounded-[14px] object-cover transition-all duration-300" height="768" loading="lazy" width="1344" src="./map_europe_states_files/45c100d8-fc91-4d84-94cc-c5b27539f518-833564cb-ce4d-4c3f-879a-6421fab23371-1777662867287-0.png"><div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/0 transition-all duration-200 group-hover:bg-black/20"><div class="absolute top-3 right-3 opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-200 group-hover:opaci